%% Scania — CIAM SSO login + JIT customer creation (POC)
%% Grounded in research-docs.md §15 Federated Authentication (Authorization Code flow, storefront JIT provisioning).
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as Fleet Customer
    participant Yves as Yves (Storefront)
    participant CIAM as CIAM (My Scania IdP)
    participant Auth as ScaniaCiamAuth<br/>(Federated Auth plugin chain)
    participant Zed as Zed (Customer + Company)
    participant DB as Database

    Note over User,DB: Native Spryker login is disabled — CIAM is the sole auth method (ADR-001)
    User->>Yves: Click "Log in with My Scania"
    Yves->>CIAM: Redirect (OAuth2 Authorization Code)
    CIAM->>User: Present My Scania login
    User->>CIAM: Authenticate
    CIAM-->>Yves: Redirect back with authorization code
    Yves->>CIAM: Exchange code for tokens
    CIAM-->>Yves: id_token + claims (email, name, company, country, roles)
    Yves->>Auth: Handle identity (provider, external_id)
    Auth->>Zed: Find customer by (provider, external_id) / email
    alt Customer exists
        Zed-->>Auth: Existing customer + company user
    else Not found — JIT provisioning
        Auth->>Zed: Create Customer + Company + Company User (from claims)
        Auth->>Zed: Map CIAM roles → Company Roles (ACL)
        Zed->>DB: Persist customer, company user, role assignment
        Note right of Zed: POC fail-fast — throw exception<br/>if creation fails (ADR-001)
        Zed-->>Auth: New customer + company user
    end
    Auth-->>Yves: Establish Spryker session (independent of IdP)
    Yves-->>User: Logged in — redirect to fleet / dashboard
